<span class="displaytext"><b><i>"(candidate full) has a sort-of a do nothing or minimalist approach, and that's not going to work." -- gov. tim pawlenty </i></b><p>gov. tim pawlenty (r-mn)<br/> fox news' "fox &amp; friends"<br/> june 24, 2008</p><p>governor tim pawlenty: "well, to be fair, i think (candidate full) has spoken in the past about off-shore drilling if the states allow it and give permission, which is what he's proposed here now. you have a situation where (candidate full)'s for reducing gas taxes for temporary relief. (candidate full)'s against that. (candidate full)'s for nuclear energy. (candidate full)'s against that. (candidate full) is for drilling now to create more supply, and we need it -- look at these gas prices. (candidate full)'s against that. (candidate full) is for not increasing taxes on energy. (candidate full) has been for increasing taxes. so there's big contrast here.</p><p>"(candidate full) sees the need to increase supply. (candidate full) has a sort-of a do nothing or minimalist approach, and that's not going to work. we have a big crisis in this country, and (candidate full) i think in terms of this offshore drilling issue has said in the past, he would look at it if states were involved, and that's what he's proposed."</p><p><b><i><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hyjj2hylcfe">watch</a> gov. tim pawlenty</i></b></p></span>



